CatDescriptText: Cutline of related article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "The Steel City Gay Northeasterners entertained, but glamorously, their six sister chapters from Baltimore, Boston, Detroit, New York, Philadelphia, and Washington, celebrating Pittsburgh's tenth anniversary...and the nation's 28th year of existence...The grand ball, held Saturday night in the Pittsburgh Room of the Penn Sheraton..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Percy Garland and Hazel Garland, pose in front of railing in the Penn Sheraton Hotel for Gay Northeasterners ball
